# Cloudflare Pages headers — No Outcome ABA games
# Cache strategy: HTML is set to no-cache by the worker (it rewrites HTML and
# injects ?v=APP_VERSION into asset URLs). Versioned CSS/JS are immutable here —
# a deploy bumps APP_VERSION, changing the URL, which busts the cache safely.
# NOTE: Cache-Control is intentionally NOT set in /* — Pages *combines* same-name
# headers across matching rules, so a /* Cache-Control would merge with the
# asset rule and produce a contradictory value. HTML caching lives in the worker.
# Security: low-risk hardening subset. A nonce-based CSP is intentionally deferred
# (games rely on inline scripts: admin-hash block, intro toggle) and staged later.

/*
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()

/*.css
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/*.js
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
